  "title": "GEOTECHNICAL ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Supervise and oversee bored piling works, ground improvement works.</li><li>Handle bored pile operation and site operation.</li><li>Collect soil sample, prepare borelog report and deal with QPS team.</li><li>Prepare and update progress report, shop drawings.</li><li>Prepare RFI.</li><li>Co-ordination work and managing subcontractors.</li><li>Liaise with the consultants on technical and quality issues.</li><li>Responsible for on-site technical and engineering matters.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Technical, Statutory, Safety and QC requirements.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering or Geological, recognized by the PE Board and BCA.</li><li>5 years of relevant Civil working experience.</li><li>Minimum 1 year completed project experience with project value of around 18 million or above.</li><li>Must have certified Piling Personnel (CPP).</li><li>Experienced in Bored Piling , ground improvement works and general site work.</li><li>Knowledge in Singapore's geological soil and rock profile and experience in LTA / Infrastructure / Government projects is added advantage.</li><li>Able to work full time at site.</li><li>Location: Changi Airport </li></ul>",
